Silulumanzi has said it is still working to fix a water leak at the Mostert Road circle, but has fixed the other water leak at the corner of Van der Merwe and Mostert. The spokesperson for Silulumanzi, Richmond Jele, said the leak at the corner of Mostert and Van der Merwe was fixed late Tuesday afternoon. He said the pavement at the repair site still needs to be rebuilt, but would be attended to. Jele went on to say that Silulumanzi is searching for the source of the leak at the circle. Repairs to fix it are in progress. ALSO SEE: Gallery: Lowveld Ramblers hike from Mac Mac Pools to Graskop Hut